===Etymology===
From {{m|en|-ary}} (taken from {{m|en|[[unary]]/[[binary]]/[[ternary]] [<nowiki/>[[function]]/[[operator]]<nowiki/>]}}) + {{affix|en|-ity}}. Compare {{m|en|adicity}} and {{m|en|adinity}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈæɹɪti/|/ˈeəɹɪti/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-arity.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|en|æɹɪti|s=3}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|logic|mathematics|computer science}} The number of [[argument]]s or [[operand]]s a [[function]] or [[operation]] takes. For a [[relation]], the number of [[domain]]s in the [[correspond]]ing [[Cartesian product]].
# {{lb|en|mathematics|computer science}} The maximum number of [[child]] nodes that any node in a given [[tree]] (data structure) may have.
# {{lb|en|Lojban|_|grammar}} the number of arguments (in [[Lojban]] [[grammar]] called [[sumti]]) specified in the definition of a [[selbri]]. (the [[selbri]] combined with the [[sumti]] make up a [[bridi]]).

